</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F99F667EE551BF59FD23BEA788661A86" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="320D888E2F713A08DFFF5D5B5F24D81D" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1DED021ECCAA1B525F593B80EE198831" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">
Endemic to the valley of the 
<normalizedToken id="67A0E6A67A173CEC0262A09589DEB86B" originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
Huancabamba (
<normalizedToken id="4BD9C09D36FC23315247A15AAD3B6972" originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
Pozuzo) in central Peru; found within the Parque Nacional Yanachaga-Chemillen (
<figureCitation id="699A48922CBBDCDAA8F2B53FBF10DB68" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Distribution of Solanum kulliwaita (circles), Solanum dillonii (triangles) and Solanum oxapampense (squares)." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/9843" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0169F6991ABDB0FB18D84DC8BBAB5E95" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="8B2CA1BD3C525FD65725EE8F9D5FA75E" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="35881B4A3712E254170C37055EFD19CA" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Montane forests from 1500 to 2500 m elevation; as with many members of the Brevantherum group, often found along roadsides and in open areas.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1A127B99EF711A4B5141E26ED5413D75" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5B746E1BBAB7101C440294D41DF5F658" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5CF6F3914BAE0F60BB73D32A2794BA73" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Named for the valley of Oxapampa, where this species is endemic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ED24375A981AD57C24FA86142D8A0ABC" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" type="preliminary conservation status">
<paragraph id="019623C7F343C648B8C82A05A77A0B21" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Preliminary conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ADEA18CC1FFBC40394CFBA8AD4251286" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName id="547E879C2AFBD94EFCC979FABAD6710B" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
is known from only 4 localities, has an EOO of 198 km2 and AOO (using a cell size of 0.04) of 195 km2; giving it a status of Endangered (
<bibRefCitation id="AB903CEB748B5CF81310F1F738757805" author="IUCN Species Survival Commision," journalOrPublisher="Caldasia" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" refId="B9" refString="IUCN Species Survival Commision, , 2001. IUCN Red List Categories: Version 3.1. IUCN, Gland and Cambridge." title="IUCN Red List Categories: Version 3.1. IUCN, Gland and Cambridge." year="2001">IUCN 2001</bibRefCitation>
). If the 
<bibRefCitation id="15BBD2EE6EBA98B04664EC626FA90464" author="IUCN Species Survival Commision," journalOrPublisher="Caldasia" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" refId="B9" refString="IUCN Species Survival Commision, , 2001. IUCN Red List Categories: Version 3.1. IUCN, Gland and Cambridge." title="IUCN Red List Categories: Version 3.1. IUCN, Gland and Cambridge." year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
recommended cell size is applied the AOO is reduced to 16 km2; the status remains Endangered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F8F71B5E3BAB450760EFAFA9BD9D6992" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="7" pageNumber="40" type="specimens examined">
<paragraph id="33A2510685B35E4F9D157CA627599FEB" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Specimens examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B3587A6A152EF3464E727710DC90760" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="F494203C473F6F33694DA7CED8D3E3EF" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="40">Peru:</emphasis>
Pasco: Prov. Oxapampa, Dist. Huancabamba, camino a Pozuzo, 1200-1400 m, 10°04.02S, 75°32.59W, 2 June 2004, R. Rojas, M. Huaman, A. 
<normalizedToken id="50983DB25D00E1BE9E2881A4A11C75AF" originalValue="Peña">Pena</normalizedToken>
&amp; J. Mateo 2490 (MO, NY [NY00824860], USM); Prov. Oxap 
<pageBreakToken id="E23EFEF6FB133C318E2CA9203426F6ED" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" start="start">ampa</pageBreakToken>
, Dist. Oxapampa, Parque Nacional Yanachaga-Chemillen, Sector Chacos, 2471, 10°37'S, 75°17'W, 24 January 2004, R. Vasquez, A. Monteagudo, A. 
<normalizedToken id="4A56D3E090D2928DC6E23F42AC06FA74" originalValue="Peña">Pena</normalizedToken>
&amp; R. Francis 28939 (MO, NY[NY00829065], USM); Prov. Oxapampa, Dist. Oxapampa, Oxapampa-Villa Rica road, 2300 m, 10°39.59S, 75°19.33W, 22 November 2007, E. Tepe, S. Stern, J. Mateo, M.P. Moreno, R. Rojas 2227 (BM [BM001017349], USM, UT).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="58BDDF53815287E9C12A75156A983D67" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="660C6A4C9DCACAF930DB0F686742E901" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BCEAA17FB19F70AA8265FC68E5AF1E1D" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName id="A14CC9B3B66DF7CF93F4F73864CCDF3F" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
is a very distinctive species with its coriaceous and strongly discolorous leaves, with the upper surfaces dark green and shiny and the veins deeply impressed, and the lower surfaces densely pubescent with pale tan peltate trichomes. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="07533E2E8257365E128FCFDA8273D2E4" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
M. Nee with which it is broadly sympatric, but does not apparently co-occur. 
<taxonomicName id="C2907DC036FCC684AA15C48E7FB73E4F" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
is found along the eastern slopes of the Andes from Ecuador to southern Peru, 
<taxonomicName id="E76E51743B8EE571DE8CED10D04EA4F5" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
is possibly derived from it. The two species share trichomes that are peltate to some degree, small white flowers and small fruits (orange in 
<taxonomicName id="0D06243F289E3515ADF5B9B9C1C5F99B" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
, apparently green at maturity in 
<taxonomicName id="F1C982379A48E37CF2531B9B7953334A" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="21AF3D13F3DBB3A11BA7A60EC175659C" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="A0E4E30BBE2644C241F3DD4D62BA3120" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
in its coriaceous, narrower leaves and in its pubescence, which is composed of truly peltate trichomes whose rays are fused for more than half their length and that lack midpoints. Trichomes of 
<taxonomicName id="4A1E0C526FFDBEAEBFA4F1180D517DC1" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
have rays that are only fused in the central half, near the midpoint; midpoints are always present, even if sometimes very small and nub-like.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="841382C41EB5BA807CDD557D2B4AF680" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
In the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="2DBB6E8ACA91D8C5D49307344DA6AAE2" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="255D81B8B96AF710846ECC3D48998FE3" author="Nee, M" journalOrPublisher="Kurtziana" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="137 - 140" refId="B19" refString="Nee, M, 2000. A new species of Solanum (Solanaceae) from Peru and Ecuador. Kurtziana 28: 137 - 140" title="A new species of Solanum (Solanaceae) from Peru and Ecuador." volume="28" year="2000">Nee 2000</bibRefCitation>
), the plant illustrated in Figure 1 is Smith &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="FF5857B96F6842523025492C89479C3D" originalValue="Albán">Alban</normalizedToken>
5558 the type specimen selected here for 
<taxonomicName id="9A8694419812605F68D86CA37D9C5753" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
, not Jaramillo et al. 13285, the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="6F6A40B6E936A4E7DEC0B28E443A39E8" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
as indicated in the text of 
<bibRefCitation id="4A60D9A99EB6FF2984E6FC16DCB1DD7B" author="Nee, M" journalOrPublisher="Kurtziana" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="137 - 140" refId="B19" refString="Nee, M, 2000. A new species of Solanum (Solanaceae) from Peru and Ecuador. Kurtziana 28: 137 - 140" title="A new species of Solanum (Solanaceae) from Peru and Ecuador." volume="28" year="2000">Nee (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. Smith and 
<normalizedToken id="C9A627EEE3362A4B3A7B84AFAB7278C7" originalValue="Albán">Alban</normalizedToken>
5558 is the only specimen of the species here recognised as 
<taxonomicName id="9C667EB698C84D5DBEC24C79D9CD761C" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
to have been included in the original circumscription of 
<taxonomicName id="CDDD2F842C59AF9BCB5715A4799F9E10" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
; an emended description of that species excluding this element is presented below and diagnostic characters separating the two are presented above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F6FA7A39C070CC517A8B662EF6F125D9" pageId="8" pageNumber="41">
Neither 
<taxonomicName id="0591CA40089995E38BC6C340779B4AD9" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampense">Solanum oxapampense</taxonomicName>
nor 
<taxonomicName id="F6386B58609F2D9988FCB904DE1A5838" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
would have been included in section 
<taxonomicName id="D2E70C4354052921816C17936F04B30E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Brevantherum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Brevantherum</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="7D96EB946A1711525F9DE57CED4EB815" author="Roe, KE" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="239 - 278" refId="B24" refString="Roe, KE, 1972. A revision of Solanum section Brevantherum (Solanaceae). Brittonia 24: 239 - 278" title="A revision of Solanum section Brevantherum (Solanaceae)." volume="24" year="1972">Roe (1972)</bibRefCitation>
due to their possession of peltate trichomes, despite the overall habit and inflorescence morphology. 
<bibRefCitation id="E97CE072E58069FFB6844C5D8A6C9E46" author="Nee, M" journalOrPublisher="Kurtziana" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="137 - 140" refId="B19" refString="Nee, M, 2000. A new species of Solanum (Solanaceae) from Peru and Ecuador. Kurtziana 28: 137 - 140" title="A new species of Solanum (Solanaceae) from Peru and Ecuador." volume="28" year="2000">Nee (2000)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned this in the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="49EC204D44B8F3F8C9C22730C9C4C72E" authorityName="M. Nee" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">Solanum verecundum</taxonomicName>
(see below). Molecular data show these groups (the traditional sections 
<taxonomicName id="E9FBF9E0F6BF239345726539410982F7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Brevantherum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Brevantherum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D46CBCF3E5F0F75691F527BBF1645349" authorityName="Hayek" authorityYear="1930" baseAuthorityName="Turrill" genus="Lepidota" lsidName="" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" rank="genus">Lepidota</taxonomicName>
(Dunal) Seithe) to be members of the same clade, defined by having ellipsoid anthers and variations on stellate trichomes (some of which have lost the rays altogether, e.g., section 
<taxonomicName id="2F7FADC030EA739BF0AE5BE1CF8D2596" authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1842" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Gonatotrichum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Gonatotrichum</taxonomicName>
Bitter, see 
<bibRefCitation id="34AE31EDA7D2094E96A2958DF333D27D" author="Stern, SR" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="503 - 510" refId="B29" refString="Stern, SR, Bohs, L, 2009. Two new species of Solanum from Ecuador and new combinations in Solanum section Pachyphylla (Solanaceae). Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas 3: 503 - 510" title="Two new species of Solanum from Ecuador and new combinations in Solanum section Pachyphylla (Solanaceae)." volume="3" year="2009">Stern and Bohs 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
